    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Case of Wen Ho Lee: The Questions Linger</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bob Yun letter criticizes Atty Gen Reno for saying Wen Ho Lee 'is no hero,' with regard to removal of security documents from Los Alamos laboratory</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Reno and Freeh, in Hearing, Defend Case Against Scientist'' (front page, Sept. 27):</p>
        <p>Attorney General Janet Reno testified before Congress and asserted that ''Dr. Lee is no hero.'' I am disappointed that the attorney general was resorting to the straw-man  tactic. No one said that Wen Ho Lee is a hero. Quite the contrary, he is a victim of racial profiling.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Reno and Freeh, in Hearing, Defend Case Against Scientist'' (front page, Sept. 27):</p>
        <p>Attorney General Janet Reno testified before Congress and asserted that ''Dr. Lee is no hero.'' I am disappointed that the attorney general was resorting to the straw-man  tactic. No one said that Wen Ho Lee is a hero. Quite the contrary, he is a victim of racial profiling.</p>
        <p>And because the executive and legislative branches of our government do not want to admit it, they choose  to focus narrowly on Dr. Lee's single guilty plea.</p>
        <p>BOB YUN  Hopewell Jct., N.Y., Sept. 28, 2000</p>
      </block>
